### 1450.

<span id="page_436">p. 436</span>

Giuliano Condi\[1\],-- <span id="fr_468"></span>[774](#fn_468.md) , As he
was 59 years old in 1480, he certainly would not have been alive at the
time of Leonardo's death. But Leonardo must have been on intimate terms
with the family till the end of his life, for in a letter dated June 1.
1519, in which Fr. Melzi, writing from Amboise, announces Leonardo's
death to Giuliano da Vinci at Florence (see p. 284), he says at the end
"*Datemene risposta per i Gondi*" (see UZIELLI, *Ricerche*, passim).

Most of the other names on the list are those of well-known Florentine
families.} Tomaso Ridolf1,-- Tomaso Paganelli,--Nicolo delNero,--Simone
Zasti,--Nasi,--the heir of Lionardo Manelli, --Guglielmo di Ser
Martino,--Bartolomeo del Tovaglia,--Andrea Arrigucci,-- Nicolo
Capponi,--Giovanni Portinari.

